The paper discusses a communication technique (sparse code multiple access) and proposes algorithmic optimizations and hardware architectures for its decoding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed optimizations and hardware architectures involve probabilistic and computational techniques, which could also place the paper in the Signal Processing (cs.SI), Architecture (cs.AR), or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
